"{\"title\": \"INTRODUCTION TO JOURNALISM\", \"level\": \"2213\", \"abbreviation\": \"WR\", \"description\": \"Cat. I. \\nThe course is for students who may wish to make careers in journalism or\\ncommunications and for those who wish to understand the history, function, production and contemporary challenges of print journalism. Students will analyze articles from newspapers, magazines and Web sites. They will learn and practice the skills of the journalist: finding the story, researching, interviewing, writing on deadline, copy-editing and proof-reading. Classes will also cover matters such as objectivity, fairness, ethics and libel, as well as wider issues of mass communication such as agenda setting, citizen journalism and the implications of converging media. To give students a more keen sense of audience, work will be read and discussed in class. Students will be urged to write for the college newspaper. Publication beyond the campus will be strongly encouraged.\", \"req\": [], \"cat1Status\": true, \"startYear\": -1}"